 query. Here's what I found:\n\n## Black-Box Query Complexity and Polynomial Summation\n\nResearch on black-box query complexity has shown that the simple upper bound of 2^n for computing polynomial summation is tight for any field in the black-box model where one has only oracle access to the polynomial.\n\n## Multiplicative Extractors and Black-Box Limitations (2024-2025)\n\nMore recently, research has shown that black-box techniques cannot yield extractors with additive error ε=n^(-ω(1)) under certain complexity-theoretic assumptions. A 2025 paper by Ronen Shaltiel on \"Multiplicative Extractors for Samplable Distributions\" was published in the 40th Computational Complexity Conference (CCC 2025).\n\n## Computational Complexity Results (2024)\n\nThe search results also include various other complexity-theoretic lower bounds from 2024, though none appear to directly combine all the terms in your specific query regarding black-box lower bounds for summatory multiplicative functions.\n\nIf you're looking for more specific research on this particular combination of topics, you may want to search the Electronic Colloquium on Computational Complexity (ECCC) or recent conference proceedings from CCC 2024-2025 directly.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"a3acde5b-ba8d-4e42-a093-b8d554abe35c","timestamp":"2026-04-04T15:12:36.449Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"5a930160-25ad-429e-be21-9c9a195ef559","userType":"external","entrypoint":"sdk-cli","cwd":"/apps/aplikacijos/prime-research","sessionId":"33140f23-a580-4bd9-95f3-32a2246a99e4","version":"2.1.92","gitBranch":"main","slug":"majestic-juggling-whale"}
